result.formatted_address: 2 Hart Ave, Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong
result.name: FATT'S PLACE

reviews.text: It was a fun atmosphere here, throwing used nut shells on the floor, like the same idea in Raffles in Singapore. I enjoyed it here, good little find.

Good place to have a few with friends, with a good view of the street to people watch. Bottomless peanuts in shells available for free, so that will explain the stuff on the floor :) One of my favourites drinking spots.

Cute, famous bar with big beer selection. Especially famous for the complimentary peanuts, with the shells all over the floor. Music very loud though, so not a very cozy place. But fun. Their burger menu also quite good.
Good place to have a beer. But the air con is not strong enough in the summer time.

Very casual place for drinking. Every one was being obsessed on peanut basket on their table which was being supplied unlimited. And on the floor, it was full of peanut hull, what a relaxed place. Beers were normal, very standard. Space was a little tight but still ok. Staffs were busy and still nice.
